			"after": " At the end of 1859 Pedro II departed on a trip to provinces north of the capital visiting Esp rito Santo Bahia Sergipe Alagoas Pernambuco and Para ba He returned in February 1860 after four months The trip was a huge success with the Emperor welcomed everywhere with warmth and joy 141 The first half of the 1860s saw peace and prosperity in Brazil Civil liberties were maintained 142 143 Freedom of speech had existed since Brazil s independence and was strongly defended by Pedro II 144 145 He found newspapers from the capital and from the provinces an ideal way to keep track of public opinion and the nation s overall situation 92 Another means of monitoring the Empire was through direct contacts with his subjects One opportunity for this was during regular Tuesday and Saturday public audiences where anyone of any social class including slaves 146 could gain admittance and present their petitions and stories 147 148 Visits to schools colleges prisons exhibitions factories barracks and other public appearances presented further opportunities to gather first hand information 149 ",
